reviews_data.review_text:
Great selections, and they offer a bunch of activities for kids and family.
My kid loves their mindful movement class
Beautiful library.  Clean, modern and very inviting. The staff is wonderful just absolutely lovely young ladies who are very nice and helpful.

This is a sweet library that is connected with Cabarrus County, so you can reserve books and pick them up here. But they also have a great selection despite being a smaller branch. They also do lots of activities for all ages. I grew up going to this library and it’s fun to bring my own children now.
Both Rowan & Mecklenburg libraries are better. This place is backwards.

This library is incredible. The book selections are spot on, especially the cookbooks. They offer a wide selection of programs for children to adults. The staff here is why this library shines. They are happy to help you find a book to even helping you solve a crochet question and everything in between. I truly cannot say enough good about this library.

Just enrolled into the library today and got to attend the 'Stories under the Stars' program - 'Discovery Place' was the topic. One of the luckiest days I would say,  Mr. Michael explained many scientific facts that were mind blowing. We thoroughly enjoyed the event as a family and looking forward for more sessions in future!
I love this place!
Super friendly staff that always help with whatever I need! And the space is lovely and welcoming!
We love Tues and Thurs Toddler story time with Miss Kimmy!

I went in to the library today and needed assistance. I would highly recommend Nya for her professional work ethic. She was the one who came and checked on me. She came to see if I needed any assistance. The other lady didn’t come out from behind the desk to see if I needed assistance after being asked. Please acknowledge Nya for her beautiful spirit and willingness to help.
Love the local library. If they don't have what you are looking for they can usually get it for you in a day or two.
Great library with very nice space for children. One suggestion is to work on completing book series. It's frustrating to start and then find out the rest of the series hasn't been included.
They are always SO helpful.
Friendly and helpful staff.  My daughter and I love all of the activities.   It encourages us both to read and learn more.
It was the drive, I am always curious about backroads,  particularly those I am not familiar with,  peaceful driving and I was surprise where it  turn out .
Quiet place to read books and computer lab
They always have the books I want, and if they don't, they'll order them!  They also have audio books...
This is the perfect library for our community! They are always doing something; the staff is extremely helpful there's so many resources there: it's impossible to be bored!
The staff is great. Great kids area with lots of things for young readers
Friendly and quiet. Plenty of workspaces near outlets to plug in and use a laptop.
Friendly and outgoing staff, fantastic resources, and an evident love for our community. Libraries like this are a lifeblood for a thriving community. I am so grateful for ours!
I love the Library everyone that works there is so very helpful. Always willing to help find a book or help you print something.
Redecorated since I  was last there. Very nice
It's a quiet, perfect place to work & study...
Not what I expected at all NO HELP

My girls and I visited this library for the first time a few weeks ago. During our hunt for amazing books we were met by Ms. Amanda, what an incredible human being! She found a book for my little girls which they absolutely loved. She spoke to is with such warmth and kindness. Today we are driving back to that library because my girls keep asking me to take them back to Ms. Amanda's library. What a gem!
I go to this library regularly.  I've always felt welcomed & am offered assistance when needed.
Very helpful
Love the resources the library offers. Avid reader
Super, friendly, helpful staff. I love the library!

Amanda, in the children's department is so wonderful!!! She is kind and sweet to each and every child and goes with them in journey for their very special book. Today, I watched the eyes of a child light up with excitement over the Star Wars section. Amanda is great!!

This place is truly amazing, its become our go to place for my son to have fun, make friends, and learn! The children's room staff in particular are beyond friendly and truly love what they do as well as taking time to get to know the children who come in. I cannot get over how wonderful this place is and how creative and exciting the events have been for my son. The only negative well...I just wish I had started coming here sooner 😊
I really like this library, but their price to print is outrageous! They charge 25 cents per sheet when they used to charge 15 cents per sheet.
Great location. Friendly staff. Clean areas & awesome selection of books.

Love that they have a Spanish Literature section!
I only wish people would be courteous and turn off their phones at the library. It's hard to read with loud ring tones and conversations.
The staff is very friendly. The kids area is clean and has lots of fun activities. It's quiet and a great place to sit and read.
Great staff. Lots of programs for children and adults. Great selection for a local library.   Preloaded tablets available on a wide range of subjects.

I have always found the library staff to be friendly, welcoming, courteous, and very helpful.  In fact, on several occasions I feel they have gone beyond the expected norm.  I believe they enjoy the journey.
Love this library. Friendly, helpful staff. Great location! Several weekly activity's for everyone in the family.
Great place
This is a great library! They have great staff who are very helpful as well as a large number of activities going on all the time! If you get the chance to stop by, do!
Great friendly staff. Very helpful.
Awesome library and librarians!
that is true, calm place. staff is very helpful and enenthusiastic.
